<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1167064679622"><term>angle of refraction</term> <meaning id="fs-id1167064630678">the angle between the normal and the refracted ray</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1167064630682"><term>critical angle</term> <meaning id="fs-id1167065073355">an incident angle that produces an angle of refraction of 90°</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1167065855707"><term>dispersion</term> <meaning id="fs-id1167065703844">separation of white light into its component wavelengths</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1167066044689"><term>incident ray</term> <meaning id="fs-id1167065020382">the incoming ray toward a medium boundary or a reflective surface</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1167064932525"><term>index of refraction</term> <meaning id="fs-id1167064986383">the speed of light in a vacuum divided by the speed of light in a given material</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1167065020906"><term>refracted ray</term> <meaning id="fs-id1167065971979">the light ray after it has been refracted</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1167065971982"><term>Snell’s law</term> <meaning id="fs-id1167066047923">the law of refraction expressed mathematically as  <m:math>
 <m:mrow>
